{"title_page": "Grygorii Vovchynskyi", "text_new": "{{Infobox skier\n| name= Grygorii Vovchynskyi\n| image = 2010 Winter Paralympics Men's Biathlon pursuit st medalists.jpg\n| caption =From left to right: Grygorii Vovchynskyi of the [[Ukraine at the 2010 Winter Paralympics|Ukraine]] (bronze), [[Kirill Mikhaylov]] of [[Russia at the 2010 Winter Paralympics|Russia]] (gold), and [[Nils-Erik Ulset]] of [[Norway at the 2010 Winter Paralympics|Norway]] (silver) with the medals they earned in [[biathlon at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 3 km pursuit]].\n| fullname = Grygorii Vasylovych Vovchynskyi\n| nickname = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1988|7|4|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = Bilousivka, [[Drabiv Raion]], [[Cherkasy Oblast]], [[Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic|Ukrainian SSR]], Soviet Union\n| height =  \n| club = \n| skis =  \n| seasons = \n| wins = \n| totalpodiums = \n| medaltemplates = \n{{Medal|Country | {{UKR}} }}\n{{Medal|Comp|[[Paralympic Games]]}}\n{{Medal|Sport | Men's [[para cross-country skiing]]}}\n{{Medal|Silver | [[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics|2010 Vancouver]]|[[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 1x4/2x5 km relay|1x4/2x5 km relay]]}}\n{{Medal|Bronze | 2010 Vancouver|[[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 10 km#Standing|10 km, standing]]}}\n{{Medal|Sport | Men's [[para biathlon]]}}\n{{Medal|Silver | [[Biathlon at the 2010 Winter Paralympics|2010 Vancouver]]|[[Biathlon at the 2010 Winter Paralympics - Men's 12.5 km individual#Standing|12.5 km, standing]]}}\n{{Medal|Bronze | 2010 Vancouver|[[Biathlon at the 2010 Winter Paralympics - Men's 3 km pursuit#Standing|men's 3 km pursuit, standing]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Grygorii Vasylovych Vovchynskyi''' ({{lang-uk|\u0413\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0456\u0439 \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0412\u043e\u0432\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439}}, born 4 July 1988)<ref name=uaparabio/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vancouver2010.com/paralympic-games/cross-country-skiing/athletes/grygorii-vovchynskyi_ath3000070ks.html |title=Grygorii Vovchynskyi |website=Vancouver2010.com |publisher=[[Vancouver Organizing Committee for the 2010 Olympic and Paralympic Winter Games]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100408221304/http://www.vancouver2010.com/paralympic-games/cross-country-skiing/athletes/grygorii-vovchynskyi_ath3000070ks.html |archive-date=2010-04-08 |url-status=dead}}</ref> is a [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] [[biathlete]], [[cross-country skier]] and [[Paralympian]]. He is classified LW8 (single arm amputation), and compete in classification category standing.\n\nHe finished the [[Cherkasy National University]] (2012).\n\nHe competed in [[Biathlon at the 2010 Winter Paralympics|biathlon]] and [[cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics]] in Vancouver, Canada. In cross-country skiing he won silver in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 1 x 4 km + 2 x 5 km Relay|men's relay, open]] with [[Iurii Kostiuk]], [[Vitaliy Lukyanenko]] and [[Volodymyr Ivanov (skier)|Volodymyr Ivanov]], and a bronze medal in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 10 km#Standing|10 km, standing]]. He placed 6th in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 1 km Sprint#Standing|men's 1 km sprint]] and 15th in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 20 km#Standing|20 km, standing]]. In biathlon, he took the silver medal in the [[Biathlon at the 2010 Winter Paralympics - Men's 12.5 km individual#Standing|12.5 km]], and the bronze medal in the [[Biathlon at the 2010 Winter Paralympics - Men's 3 km pursuit#Standing|men's 3 km pursuit, standing]].<ref name=ipc>{{IPC profile|surname=Vovchynskyi|givenname=Grygorii}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=uaparabio>{{cite web | url = http://www.paralympic.org.ua/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=527&Itemid=107 | script-title=uk:\u0412\u043e\u0432\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0413\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0456\u0439 \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 | language = Ukrainian |trans-title=Grygorii Vasylovych Vovchynskyi | publisher = paralympic.org.ua | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140308193359/http://www.paralympic.org.ua/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=527&Itemid=107 | archivedate = 8 March 2014 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IPC athlete|id=grygorii-vovchynskyi|old_id=917562}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vovchynskyi, Grygorii}}\n[[Category:Ukrainian male cross-country skiers]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian male biathletes]]\n[[Category:Paralympic biathletes of Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Paralympic cross-country skiers of Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Biathletes at the 2010 Winter Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Cross-country skiers at the 2010 Winter Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Paralympic silver medalists for Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Paralympic bronze medalists for Ukraine]]\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Drabiv Raion]]\n[[Category:Biathletes at the 2014 Winter Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2010 Winter Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2014 Winter Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Biathletes at the 2018 Winter Paralympics]]\n\n\n{{Ukraine-biathlon-bio-stub}}\n{{Ukraine-Paralympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox skier\n| name= Grygorii Vovchynskyi\n| image = 2010 Winter Paralympics Men's Biathlon pursuit st medalists.jpg\n| caption =From left to right: Grygorii Vovchynskyi of the [[Ukraine at the 2010 Winter Paralympics|Ukraine]] (bronze), [[Kirill Mikhaylov]] of [[Russia at the 2010 Winter Paralympics|Russia]] (gold), and [[Nils-Erik Ulset]] of [[Norway at the 2010 Winter Paralympics|Norway]] (silver) with the medals they earned in [[biathlon at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 3 km pursuit]].\n| fullname = Grygorii Vasylovych Vovchynskyi\n| nickname = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1988|7|4|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = Bilousivka, [[Drabiv Raion]], [[Cherkasy Oblast]], [[Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic|Ukrainian SSR]], Soviet Union\n| height =  \n| club = \n| skis =  \n| seasons = \n| wins = \n| totalpodiums = \n| medaltemplates = \n{{Medal|Country | {{UKR}} }}\n{{Medal|Comp|[[Paralympic Games]]}}\n{{Medal|Sport | Men's [[para cross-country skiing]]}}\n{{Medal|Silver | [[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics|2010 Vancouver]]|[[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 1x4/2x5 km relay|1x4/2x5 km relay]]}}\n{{Medal|Bronze | 2010 Vancouver|[[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 10 km#Standing|10 km, standing]]}}\n{{Medal|Sport | Men's [[para biathlon]]}}\n{{Medal|Silver | [[Biathlon at the 2010 Winter Paralympics|2010 Vancouver]]|[[Biathlon at the 2010 Winter Paralympics - Men's 12.5 km individual#Standing|12.5 km, standing]]}}\n{{Medal|Bronze | 2010 Vancouver|[[Biathlon at the 2010 Winter Paralympics - Men's 3 km pursuit#Standing|men's 3 km pursuit, standing]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Grygorii Vasylovych Vovchynskyi''' ({{lang-uk|\u0413\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0456\u0439 \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0412\u043e\u0432\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439}}, born 4 July 1988)<ref name=uaparabio/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vancouver2010.com/paralympic-games/cross-country-skiing/athletes/grygorii-vovchynskyi_ath3000070ks.html |title=Grygorii Vovchynskyi |website=Vancouver2010.com |publisher=[[Vancouver Organizing Committee for the 2010 Olympic and Paralympic Winter Games]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100408221304/http://www.vancouver2010.com/paralympic-games/cross-country-skiing/athletes/grygorii-vovchynskyi_ath3000070ks.html |archive-date=2010-04-08 |url-status=dead}}</ref> is a [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] [[biathlete]], [[cross-country skier]] and [[Paralympian]]. He is classified LW8 (single arm amputation), and compete in classification category standing.\n\nHe finished the [[Cherkasy National University]] (2012).\n\nHe competed in [[Biathlon at the 2010 Winter Paralympics|biathlon]] and [[cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics]] in Vancouver, Canada. In cross-country skiing he won silver in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 1 x 4 km + 2 x 5 km Relay|men's relay, open]] with [[Iurii Kostiuk]], [[Vitaliy Lukyanenko]] and [[Volodymyr Ivanov (skier)|Volodymyr Ivanov]], and a bronze medal in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 10 km#Standing|10 km, standing]]. He placed 6th in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 1 km Sprint#Standing|men's 1 km sprint]] and 15th in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2010 Winter Paralympics \u2013 Men's 20 km#Standing|20 km, standing]]. In biathlon, he took the silver medal in the [[Biathlon at the 2010 Winter Paralympics - Men's 12.5 km individual#Standing|12.5 km]], and the bronze medal in the [[Biathlon at the 2010 Winter Paralympics - Men's 3 km pursuit#Standing|men's 3 km pursuit, standing]].<ref name=ipc>{{IPC profile|surname=Vovchynskyi|givenname=Grygorii}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=uaparabio>{{cite web | url = http://www.paralympic.org.ua/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=527&Itemid=107 | script-title=uk:\u0412\u043e\u0432\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0413\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0456\u0439 \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 | language = Ukrainian |trans-title=Grygorii Vasylovych Vovchynskyi | publisher = paralympic.org.ua | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140308193359/http://www.paralympic.org.ua/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=527&Itemid=107 | archivedate = 8 March 2014 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{